create_time.description: The timestamp of when the Index was created in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits.

display_name.description: The display name of the ReasoningEngine.

name.description: The generated name of the ReasoningEngine, in the format 'projects/{project}/locations/{location}/reasoningEngines/{reasoningEngine}'

region.description: The region of the reasoning engine. eg us-central1

update_time.description: The timestamp of when the Index was last updated in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits.

kms_key_name.description: Required. The Cloud KMS resource identifier of the customer managed encryption key used to protect a resource. Has the form: projects/my-project/locations/my-region/keyRings/my-kr/cryptoKeys/my-key. The key needs to be in the same region as where the compute resource is created.

block.description: Optional. Customer-managed encryption key spec for a ReasoningEngine. If set, this ReasoningEngine and all sub-resources of this ReasoningEngine will be secured by this key.

agent_framework.description: Optional. The OSS agent framework used to develop the agent.

class_methods.description: Optional. Declarations for object class methods in OpenAPI specification format.

service_account.description: Optional. The service account that the Reasoning Engine artifact runs as. It should have "roles/storage.objectViewer" for reading the user project's Cloud Storage and "roles/aiplatform.user" for using Vertex extensions. If not specified, the Vertex AI Reasoning Engine service Agent in the project will be used.

name.description: The name of the environment variable. Must be a valid C identifier.

value.description: Variables that reference a $(VAR_NAME) are expanded using the previous defined environment variables in the container and any service environment variables. If a variable cannot be resolved, the reference in the input string will be unchanged. The $(VAR_NAME) syntax can be escaped with a double $$, ie: $$(VAR_NAME). Escaped references will never be expanded, regardless of whether the variable exists or not.

block.description: Optional. Environment variables to be set with the Reasoning Engine deployment.

name.description: The name of the environment variable. Must be a valid C identifier.

secret.description: The name of the secret in Cloud Secret Manager. Format: {secret_name}.

version.description: The Cloud Secret Manager secret version. Can be 'latest' for the latest version, an integer for a specific version, or a version alias.

block.description: Reference to a secret stored in the Cloud Secret Manager that will provide the value for this environment variable.

Optional. Environment variables where the value is a secret in Cloud Secret Manager. To use this feature, add 'Secret Manager Secret Accessor' role (roles/secretmanager.secretAccessor) to AI Platform Reasoning Engine service Agent.
Optional. The specification of a Reasoning Engine deployment.

dependency_files_gcs_uri.description: Optional. The Cloud Storage URI of the dependency files in tar.gz format.

pickle_object_gcs_uri.description: Optional. The Cloud Storage URI of the pickled python object.

requirements_gcs_uri.description: Optional. The Cloud Storage URI of the requirements.txt file

block.description: Optional. User provided package spec of the ReasoningEngine. Ignored when users directly specify a deployment image through deploymentSpec.first_party_image_override, but keeping the field_behavior to avoid introducing breaking changes.
